id: jf-lpki
title: Enforce docstring and static analysis quality gates
description: "Require complete high-quality source API documentation and strict non-bypassable checks for TypeScript safety, docstrings, duplication, pm metadata, dependencies, containers/filesystems, shell scripts, PowerShell, CodeQL/Greptile, and coverage reporting."
type: Feature
status: open
priority: 0
tags[4]: code-quality,docs,security,static-analysis
created_at: "2026-07-21T19:13:36.782Z"
updated_at: "2026-07-23T05:14:21.403Z"
author: codex-jellyfin
estimated_minutes: 720
acceptance_criteria: "Every exported and internal source declaration has accurate actionable API documentation and docstring coverage is 100 percent; No any, inline/dynamic imports, non-erasable TypeScript syntax, or untyped external APIs remain; ESLint, jscpd, pm validation/lint, Trivy, ShellCheck, PSScriptAnalyzer where applicable, CodeQL, Greptile, and Codecov are mandatory documented gates; All tools are pinned, free to run in GitHub, and cannot be silently skipped when applicable files exist"
goal: jf-mqpo
value: Turn project quality policy into executable and reviewable guarantees.
impact: "Prevents undocumented, duplicated, insecure, or weakly typed changes from entering main."
outcome: A strict local and CI quality pipeline with 100 percent documentation evidence.
why_now: The new mandatory policy expands the release contract beyond runtime correctness and coverage.
parent: jf-gn5j
reviewer: maintainer
risk: critical
confidence: medium
sprint: jellyfin-10.11.11
blocked_by: jf-mkzh
